# {{PROJECT_NAME}} — environment example
#
# Copy to .env (gitignored) and fill in values. This file lists every env var
# the project reads at runtime, with a short description and an obviously-fake
# placeholder.
#
# Conventions:
# - Real secrets go in .env (which is in .gitignore). NEVER commit .env.
# - Each entry: a `#` comment describing what the var is + KEY=placeholder
# - Group by concern (database, auth, external APIs, feature flags, etc.)
# - Placeholder values must be obviously fake (e.g., `replace_me`, `sk_live_REPLACE_ME`)
#   so a real secret committed by mistake stands out at code-review.
#
# When the project's env-var reads change, update this file IN THE SAME PR.
# A `.env.example` out of sync with `process.env.*` calls is a stale-spec failure mode.

